00:54:16.159 --> 00:54:23.159
and it spoke about writing your resumes for an algorithm or AI system,

00:54:23.159 --> 00:54:27.159
as opposed to a resume that would be evaluated by humans.

00:54:28.159 --> 00:54:32.159
So I'm really, really interested in finding out, anybody,

00:54:32.159 --> 00:54:38.159
your thoughts on that whole situation in terms of tweaking your resumes

00:54:38.159 --> 00:54:46.159
to be evaluated by an AI system as opposed to a human being.

00:54:46.159 --> 00:54:50.159
I don't know if David would want to take the first go.

00:54:50.159 --> 00:54:56.159
You know, it's interesting because I know that a lot of people

00:54:56.159 --> 00:55:01.159
have written, well, at least to do that certification process

00:55:01.159 --> 00:55:03.159
that I talked about earlier where you capture,

00:55:03.159 --> 00:55:06.159
you're making sure that your resume catches all of the different objectives

00:55:06.159 --> 00:55:09.159
or requirements within the announcement.

00:55:09.159 --> 00:55:12.159
That's kind of writing towards an algorithm because you want to capture it

00:55:12.159 --> 00:55:16.159
because there is a kind of a tool they utilize to make sure that they find

00:55:16.159 --> 00:55:17.159
those things in there.

00:55:17.159 --> 00:55:20.159
So a lot of times you've got to make sure it's just basically a keyword-based

00:55:20.159 --> 00:55:23.159
capability, that that keyword show up in both areas.

00:55:23.159 --> 00:55:25.159
So that's kind of writing to it.

00:55:25.159 --> 00:55:31.159
In the end, it's still a human that's got to read through it.

00:55:31.159 --> 00:55:35.159
And you really need to be able to write to the job and the human is going to

00:55:35.159 --> 00:55:40.159
look at it and try to get, feel that you really want this position

00:55:40.159 --> 00:55:45.159
or this is somebody that really would be a good fit.

00:55:45.159 --> 00:55:47.159
And you can't do that with an algorithm, at least not yet.

00:55:47.159 --> 00:55:49.159
I don't think you can.

00:55:49.159 --> 00:55:51.159
And you're going to need to understand what that person is trying to get

00:55:51.159 --> 00:55:53.159
across.

00:55:53.159 --> 00:56:00.159
But a lot of it comes also back down to the interview process itself.

00:56:00.159 --> 00:56:01.159
So I don't know.

00:56:01.159 --> 00:56:03.159
I mean, I'm torn a little bit of both.

00:56:03.159 --> 00:56:08.159
I mean, I think there's benefits in using the algorithms to help narrow the

00:56:08.159 --> 00:56:11.159
selection down, but it's still going to come down to a human making

00:56:11.159 --> 00:56:17.159
the final decision.

