00:56:41.159 --> 00:56:48.159
Do you guys use analytics to determine which company gets a contract

00:56:48.159 --> 00:56:52.159
like SpaceX versus Amazon and stuff like that?

00:56:52.159 --> 00:56:59.159
Or is there some sort of AI that gives you indicators to go with this

00:56:59.159 --> 00:57:03.159
sort of technology instead of another type of technology?

00:57:03.159 --> 00:57:05.159
Not yet.

00:57:05.159 --> 00:57:10.159
And primarily because those are protestable issues.

00:57:10.159 --> 00:57:12.159
So when you do a contract within the U.S.

00:57:13.159 --> 00:57:19.159
government and a company, many companies apply for that contract.

00:57:19.159 --> 00:57:22.159
And their selection is made.

00:57:22.159 --> 00:57:26.159
There are many ways the people who didn't get the contract can protest

00:57:26.159 --> 00:57:28.159
that.

00:57:28.159 --> 00:57:32.159
And that is an easy area right now to say I'm going to protest that AI

00:57:32.159 --> 00:57:34.159
that was utilized.

00:57:34.159 --> 00:57:36.159
And that would slow things down a lot.

00:57:36.159 --> 00:57:41.159
So legal has basically said that's not something we should or could be

00:57:41.159 --> 00:57:43.159
doing right now.

00:57:43.159 --> 00:57:46.159
But that being said, that doesn't mean we're not looking at it.

00:57:46.159 --> 00:57:50.159
Not to make the decision, but as an indicator to weigh it, right?

00:57:50.159 --> 00:57:52.159
That's what I meant.

